{{Infobox feature on celestial object |name = Challenger Colles |image = |caption = |type = [[Collis (planetary nomenclature)|colles]] |location = [[Pluto]] |latitude = |N_or_S = |longitude = |E_or_W = |globe = |coordinates_footnotes = |length = 60 km |width = 35 km |diameter = |depth = |area = |dimensions = |peak = |discoverer = ''[[New Horizons]]'' |naming = [[Space Shuttle Challenger|Space Shuttle ''Challenger'']] |eponym = }}
'''Challenger Colles''' is a range of hills on [[Pluto]] in [[Sputnik Planitia]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.nasa.gov/feature/pluto-s-mysterious-floating-hills|title= Pluto’s Mysterious, Floating Hills|last1= Talbert|first1= Tricia|last2= |first2= |date= 4 February 2016|website= nasa.gov|publisher= [[NASA]]|access-date= 28 May 2016|quote=}}</ref> It was discovered by the ''[[New Horizons]]'' spacecraft in July 2015. It is named in honor of the [[Space Shuttle Challenger|Space Shuttle ''Challenger'']], which was [[Space Shuttle Challenger disaster|destroyed along with all seven astronauts aboard]] on January 28, 1986.
