'''EarthEcho International''' is an [[Environmentalism|environmental]] [[nonprofit]] organization founded in honor of oceanographer [[Philippe Cousteau]], by his children and widow. EarthEcho is based in [[Washington, D.C.]] The foundation was originally named the Philippe Cousteau Foundation, but changed its name after a dispute with the [[Cousteau Society]].<ref> {{cite news |last1=Argetsinger |first1=Amy |last2=Roberts |first2=Roxanne |date=2006-09-17 |title=Reliable Sources:Philippe Cousteau, Immersed in His Work |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/09/17/AR2006091700302.html |work=Washington Post |page=D03}}</ref>
One of EarthEcho's outreach activities is the "[[EarthEcho Water Challenge]]," formerly called "World Water Monitoring Day," an annual event promoting citizen [[water quality monitoring|monitoring]] of their local water resources.<ref name="monitoring challenge">{{cite web |url=http://www.worldwatermonitoringday.org |title=EarthEcho Water Challenge |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |publisher=EarthEcho International |location=Washington, D.C. |access-date=2018-04-08}}</ref>
